(CI fails because of a linter warning: I just pushed a trivial fix.)
Can you add some `assert_not_exists` to show the progress made on import reduction?
I'm not sure which of the newly available `assert_not_exists` I want to fix for the future. @YaelDillies Do you have preferences?
What files are not imported by Data.Nat.Log anymore? I tried getting the info myself but failed. Within these, is there an obvious one that should not be imported in Data.Nat.Log ever again?

<details>
<summary>Mathlib files no longer imported by `Data.Nat.Log`</summary>


- "Mathlib.Data.Option.Defs",
- "Mathlib.Data.Set.Basic",
- "Mathlib.Data.Set.Operations",
- "Mathlib.Data.Set.Subsingleton",
- "Mathlib.Data.Sigma.Basic",
- "Mathlib.Data.SProd",
- "Mathlib.Data.Sum.Basic",
- "Mathlib.Lean.Elab.Tactic.Basic",
- "Mathlib.Lean.Meta.Basic",
- "Mathlib.Logic.Equiv.Basic",
- "Mathlib.Logic.OpClass",
- "Mathlib.Order.BooleanAlgebra",
- "Mathlib.Order.BoundedOrder",
- "Mathlib.Order.Disjoint",
- "Mathlib.Order.Heyting.Basic",
- "Mathlib.Order.Interval.Set.Basic",
- "Mathlib.Order.MinMax",
- "Mathlib.Order.PropInstances",
- "Mathlib.Order.SymmDiff",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.ByContra",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.CasesM",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.CC",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.CC.Addition",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.CC.Datatypes",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.CC.Lemmas",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.DeriveToExpr",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.FBinop",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.GeneralizeProofs",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.Lift",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.Relation.Rfl",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.Relation.Symm",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.Says",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.Tauto",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.ToExpr",
- "Mathlib.Tactic.ToLevel",
- "Mathlib.Util.Delaborators",
- "Mathlib.Util.WhatsNew",
</details>
Many of them are tactics.
Nothing in this list jumps out as particularly advanced. Do we really want to do this split?
I like the idea of moving definitions to files with minimal imports. Why not?
The imports are already pretty minimal in the non-def file, so I don't really get the point, no.

![before](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a92c5204-ee2a-4a69-9f05-6976f52e1248)
![after](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f24a5ad9-9834-480d-a11e-56fcfc0fa0e3)

Hence adding `assert_not_exists OrderTop` in `Data.Nat.Log` is good here (and this opens the possibility of making `Nat.Log` even more basic. `Set.Basic` is too big, so this is good progress.
